14 guests from the worlds of rock, pop, blues, and country join Jerry Lee Lewis for an exhilarating, unforgettable evening of rock and roll. Captured on an intimate soundstage in New York City, Last Man Standing Live showcases the one and only "Killer" thrilling an audience of friends and fans. 

This special DVD release follows on the phenomenal success of last year's Last Man Standing: The Duets, which earned Jerry Lee Lewis unanimous, worldwide critical acclaim.

Last Man Standing Live brings to life the galvanizing synergy shared between Lewis and his duet partners. In addition to the 28 once-in-a-lifetime performances caught on film, exciting archival footage and candid anecdotes by Lewis' peers tell the story behind the man who was catapulted to stardom (along with Johnny Cash, Carl Perkins, and Elvis Presley) from Sun Studios in Memphis. 

In a rare, on-screen interview, Jerry Lee Lewis shares insight about his long and controversial career.
Last Man Standing Live is the rock and roll event of the year!
